HEADWORD: Minaret
<hw>Min"a*ret</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp.
<ets>minarete</ets>, Ar. <ets>man⟦amac⟧rat</ets> lamp, lantern,
lighthouse, turret, fr. <ets>n⟦amac⟧r</ets> to shine.]</ety>
<fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>A slender, lofty tower attached to a mosque and
surrounded by one or more projecting balconies, from which the summon to
prayer is cried by the muezzin.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Minargent</ent>⟦br⟧
